Food delivery from Foodloft Chidlom Thailand

Foodloft Chidlom is unique in that it is an international food court-style restaurant which is able to provide the best and most popular dishes from a range of restaurants. Cuisines on offer include Italian, Chinese, Indian, Vietnamese, Thai, Korean, Japanese, Lebanese and Western-style food. Foodloft has locations all around Thailand, including this branch in Central Chidlom plus additional restaurants in CentralPlaza Chaengwattana, Central Ladprao and CentralPlaza Pattaya Beach.

Popular dishes from Foodloft Chidlom

The Foodloft Chidlom menu is varied and large and is bound to provide something to satisfy everyone's tastes. Italian dishes include the Caesar Pizza and Lasagna Bolognese, while salads and sandwiches include the Mediterranean Salad with Tuna and Roasted Eggplant, Tomato and Chili Paste on Multi-Grain Baguette. The Chinese menu features Hong Kong-Style Shrimp Wonton Soup and Roasted Duck over Rice, while Vietnamese dishes include Pho with Pork or Chicken and the Ho Chi Minh City Set. Thai dishes include Papaya Salad with Pickled Crabs and Tom Yum Noodles with River Prawns, while Indian options include Lamb Curry and Chicken Tikka. The Korean menu features Kimchi Jijge Jeongsik and Bibimbab and Japanese offerings include Salmon Teppan Yaki and California Maki. Lebanese dishes include Lamb Spring Rolls and the Falafel Sandwich and for noodle-lovers, choose from Noodles with Poached Snapper Fillet in Broth and Braised Chicken Noodles. Finally, finish off with something sweet such as the Banana Chocolate Bread Pudding or Black Sesame Dumplings in Ginger Tea.

Menu highlights include:

  • ✓ Vietnamese-Style Rice Noodles: This convenient and healthy set features fresh rice noodles, grilled pork, pork meatballs, fried spring rolls and accompaniments.
  • ✓ Butter Chicken: An Indian classic, this dish features pieces of tender chicken in a rich and delicious sauce made from butter, tomato and cashew paste.
  • ✓ Hummus: A popular creamy Lebanese dip made with pureed chickpeas, white sesame paste and lemon juice, drizzled with olive oil.
